            "body": "> to support plugins that depend on the existing semantics, maybe create BufUnlisted that they can use instead\r\n\r\nBut the inverse is also true already: plugins that want to distinguish `BufDelete` between \"unlisted\" vs \"actually deleted\" can check `bufloaded(@%)` and `buflisted(@%)`. \r\n\r\n```vim\r\nau BufDelete * echom bufloaded(@%) buflisted(@%)\r\nsetlocal nobuflisted \" 1 0\r\nedit foo\r\nbdelete              \" 1 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nChanging this would be a \"lateral move\" in terms of capabilities, possibly a minor improvement in terms of interface, and a major cost in terms of ecosystem. Thus low leverage.",
